curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13273' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM6012", "table_name": "PIN DESCRIPTION", "content": "PIN DESCRIPTION  PIN  NAME  FUNCTION  1  RUN  Control Input. More than 1.5V input enables the device. Less than 0.3V input shuts down the  device. In shutdown, all functions stopped with the drawing supply current less than 1µA. Do  not leave it floating.  2  GND  Ground.  3  SW  Switch Node. Put an inductor to this pin and connect to the drains of the internal main and  synchronous power MOSFET switches.  4  VIN  Supply Voltage Pin. A 4.7µF ceramic capacitor or greater is used to decouple this pin to GND  closely.  5  VFB  Feedback Pin. This pin receives the feedback voltage from an external resistive divider across  the output. For adjustable version, the internal voltage divider is disabled. (SGM6012-ADJ)       1.6MHz, 800mA Synchronous  SGM6012  Step-Down Converter      4  MARCH 2016 SG Micro Corp  www.sg-micro.com  "}'
